Web:
Node, Express, React

React frontend for access on web (Firebase)
- password protected (authentification)
- view all info on searchable table

Express API hosted within Firebase Cloud Functions
API:
GET   /:group/all/:timestamp   => Return information for updates after timestamp
PATCH /:group/all   => Update information for all people

GET   /:group/:id   => Return information for that person
POST  /:group      => Add information for new person
PATCH /:group/:id   => Update information for person

Database schema:
Last updated timestamp/Date
First name
last name
age/birth day
weight
height
blood pressure: int
current meds: list of strings
symptoms: list of strings

React native GET -> Express API:

React native PATCH -> Express API:
Pass a list of all updates:
[{ firstname: _, lastname: _, birthday: _, weight: _, height: _, bloodpressure:
_, meds: _, symptoms: _, currentdate: _, notes: _ }, ...]

GET /:group/all/:timestamp   => Return information for updates after timestamp
1. Grab list of timestamps from groups/:groupid
2. For each timestamp that is later than the "Last synced" timestamp
  ("Last synced" is property of the tablet)
  - Get list of updates from groups/:timestamp and consolidate into one list

PATCH /:group/all   => Update information for all people
- Body contains list of user updates
Go through list and patch each user individually:

ihc-database.firebaseio.com/
  groups/:groupid
    timestamps when last updated ("Send updates" button on tablet was clicked)
  groups/:timestamp
    list of updates at that timestamp

ihc-database.firebaseio.com/
  groups/:groupid
    firstname, lastname, birthday

  /users/:firstnamelastnamebirthdayhash
    weight, height, blood pressure, meds, symptoms, current date, misc notes

Local:
`npm run build` from IHC/web/public/client to build React

Pipeline:
`git push`
`npm run build` from IHC/web/react
`firebase deploy` from IHC/web

